Reasoning: 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper deals with optimizing the performance of continuous-time stochastic systems, which falls under the scope of this sub-category.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a method for synthesizing optimal values of parameters, which can be seen as an AI problem.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper involves approximating optimal values using a Markov decision process, which is a common technique in machine learning.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper proposes an algorithmic approach for optimizing the performance of stochastic systems.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper may be of interest to software engineers who are developing systems that involve stochastic processes.
